        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Loss of the scaffold protein CASK increases the frequency of spontaneous excitatory release events, while spontaneous inhibitory release events are decreased. CASK loss does not affect evoked release.. Experimental description: This study used wild-type and knock-out mice" ;
